The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Glamorgan need 213 

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Glamorgan were set a target of 213 to win against Somerset in the Twenty20 Cup match at Taunton Monday. Put into bat, Somerset made 212 for three, according to information received here. 

James Hildreth top-scored with 71 off only 37 deliveries with the help of seven boundaries and three sixes. Hildreth shared a 113-run third wicket stand with K. Parsons, who remained unbeaten on 57. 

Team India captain Sourav Ganguly bowled an over, conceding 16 runs. 




